The Delta State House of Assembly has confirmed Barrister Otto Aghoghophia as Deputy Clerk. Appreciated by the workers, his colleagues and lawmakers, Otto, a professional of immense reputation, was appointed Director, Legal Matters of the assembly in 2007. Very uncompromising in matters of justice, Otto administered the legal department wisely and elegantly. Born December 18, 1973, Otto attended St. Vincent College, Okwagbe and Edo State University, Ekpoma. The great lover of correct conduct and fairness towards all persons as well as a stickler for the rule of law was called to the bar in 2000, 